The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 February is 39,165 (4,533.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 929 new confirmed cases (107.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 February, there were 1,383 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (454 fewer cases).
